Health workers fill out documents before performing tests for COVID-19 coronavirus on other health workers at the screening and testing tents set up at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Johannesburg, on April 15, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Seven more people have died of COVID-19 in South Africa bringing the total number to 138. The number of confirmed cases is up to 7220. That's an increase of 437 cases. The country has recorded 2746 recoveries. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize released the latest updated information on Monday night. So far, 2,746 people have recovered from the virus. Health Media Release 4 May ... by Travis Richards on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.